PROMPT DRAFT START\
\
You are classifying already-detected sheet-music measures.\
\
Important rules\
- You are NOT detecting measures.\
- You are NOT finding barlines.\
- You are NOT renumbering music.\
- The backend already gives the true measures and their order.\
- Each crop contains exactly one already-detected measure.\
- Do NOT infer extra measures from rhythmic groupings, repeat dots, double barlines, or edge decorations.\
- Measures are provided in left-to-right order within one system.\
- A numeric time signature is two vertically stacked meter numbers immediately after the clef/key signature, such as 2 over 4.\
- In grand-staff or piano crops, the same time signature may appear on both staves; use the shared meter for the whole measure.\
- Ignore fingering/count numbers near notes, above the staff, or below the staff. They are not time signatures.\
- If a clearly visible new time signature appears at a measure, update the active time signature from that measure onward.\
- If a new time signature is unclear or only partly visible, keep the previous active time signature.\
- Only allow pickup when is_first_measure_of_score = true.\
- If is_first_measure_of_score = false, do not label pickup.\
- Default to normal when uncertain about completeness.\
- Only label pickup if the first measure is obviously and visually incomplete, meaning it clearly contains fewer beats than a full measure and there is no plausible way it could fill the time signature.\
- For grand-staff/piano crops, judge pickup by the whole vertical measure across both staves. Do not require both staves to play notes: notes in one staff plus rests or silence in the other can still be a pickup. If the opening measure is shorter than the active time signature, mark it pickup/incomplete. Example: in 3/4, one beat before the first barline is a pickup even if only the treble staff plays. Do not mark pickup merely because one staff is sparse when the full vertical measure lasts the complete meter.\
- If you cannot confidently confirm incompleteness, label normal, not pickup.\
- If not confident overall, use uncertain rather than guessing.\
- Classify conservatively.\
\
Allowed labels\
- normal\
- pickup\
- multi_measure_rest\
- uncertain\
\
Definitions\
- normal: regular counted measure\
- pickup: true incomplete lead-in at the very beginning of the score\
- A whole note, two half notes, or other sparse-looking content in the first measure is usually a slow full measure, not a pickup. Do not label pickup just because the first measure looks sparse or simple.\
- multi_measure_rest: a true multi-measure rest with a visible count of 2 or more\
- uncertain: use when the crop is unclear, ambiguous, or not reliable enough\
\
Multi-measure rest guidance\
- A multi-measure rest has a visible count number above the staff and a rest symbol centered in the measure.\
- Do NOT require only the modern thick H-bar shape.\
- The rest symbol may appear in several forms:\
  - Modern style: one thick horizontal rectangle centered on the middle staff line\
  - Old style: a horizontal bar plus one or more vertical bars\
- In the old style, the vertical bars may be short or long, and there may be more than one.\
- If a clear count number of 2 or more is visible AND an old-style or modern multi-rest symbol is present AND no melodic content is visible, label multi_measure_rest.\
- A visible count of 2 or more above that old-style symbol is strong evidence for multi_measure_rest.\
- If the count number is clear but the symbol is unclear, return uncertain with maybe_label multi_measure_rest.\
- If the symbol is present but the count number is cut off or unreadable, return uncertain.\
- A confident multi_measure_rest label requires a clearly readable count number of 2 or more. Without a visible count number, return uncertain.\
- A visible count of 1 means the measure is normal, not multi_measure_rest.\
- A plain one-measure rest without the old-style vertical-bar structure is normal, not multi_measure_rest.\
- For grand-staff/piano crops, return multi_measure_rest only if both staves clearly share the same multi-measure rest count. If one staff has music, no count, or a different count, do not return multi_measure_rest.\
\
Conservative rules\
- A wrong confident answer is worse than uncertain.\
- Do not invent measures.\
- Do not skip any provided measure_id.\
- Do not output labels outside the allowed set.\
- Only provide rest_count when label is multi_measure_rest.\
- If label is multi_measure_rest, rest_count must be an integer >= 2.\
- If label is not multi_measure_rest, rest_count must be null.\
- If a measure might be a multi-measure rest but the count is unclear, return uncertain.\
- If a measure might be a pickup but could instead be a slow full measure, ornament, grace-note figure, or unclear fragment, return normal or uncertain, not pickup.\
- When in doubt between pickup and normal, always choose normal.\
- If suspicious_auxiliary is true, be extra conservative.\
\
Confidence values\
- high\
- medium\
- low\
\
Task\
- Classify every provided measure.\
- Treat each crop as one measure only.\
- First-measure crops may include clef, key signature, or time signature context; those are still part of that same one measure.\
- Return JSON only.\
- Do not return markdown or explanation text.\
- Every input measure_id must appear exactly once.\
\
